<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-13764] SelectTest.testMixedTTLOnColumnsWide is flaky</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13764</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;org.apache.cassandra.cql3.validation.operations.SelectTest.testMixedTTLOnColumnsWide&lt;/tt&gt; is flaky. This is because it inserts rows and then asserts their contents using &lt;tt&gt;ttl()&lt;/tt&gt; in the select, but if the test is sufficiently slow, the remaining ttl may change by the time the select is run. Anecdotally, &lt;tt&gt;testSelectWithAlias&lt;/tt&gt; in the same class uses a fudge factor of 1 second that would fix all the failures I&apos;ve seen, but it might make more sense to measure the elapsed time in the test and calculate the acceptable variation from that time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
